FT  05 AUG 93 / Households spend pounds 15 a week more
THE AVERAGE household's expenditure rose by nearly pounds 15 a week last
year in spite of the recession, according to the government's Family
Expenditure Survey.
Average weekly expenditure in 1992 was pounds 271.80, compared with pounds
256.90 in 1991. The average gross household income was pounds 342.90 per
week, compared with pounds 338.20 a year earlier.
Housing and food were the biggest items of expenditure, each accounting for
more than pounds 47 per week.
